JS cheat codes

Interview Advice (Important)
     - Use Map instead of {} when keys aren’t strings
     - Avoid forEach when you need return
     - sort() without comparator is a trap
     - Prefer while for pointers & windows
     - Arrays = stack / queue in JS





Array 
1) slice(start, end) → non-mutating
     arr.slice(1, 4); // [index 1,2,3]
      arr.slice();    // copy array

2) splice(start, deleteCount, ...items) → mutates
  The splice() method of Array instances changes the contents of an array by removing or replacing
  existing elements and/or adding new elements in place

    arr.splice(2, 1);        // remove 1 element at index 2
    arr.splice(2, 0, 10);   // insert 10 at index 2
    arr.splice(1, 2, 5, 6); // replace 2 elements at 3

3) arr.push(4); // add end
   arr.pop();   // remove end

4) arr.unshift(1) => is a method call that adds the value 1 to the beginning of the arr array. 
The original arr array is modified (mutated) in place. 


5) Iteration Methods (Very Common)
   arr.map(x => x * 2);
     arr.filter(x => x > 0);
     arr.reduce((acc, curr) => acc + curr, 0);

6) Sort 
     arr.sort((a, b) => a - b); // ascending
     arr.sort((a, b) => b - a); // descending

     string sort 
     str.split('').sort().join('');

7) String manipulations
   str.split('').reverse().join('');

8) Hashmap
     let map = new Map();
     map.set(key, value)
     map.get(key)
     map.has(key)
     map.delete(key);
     for (let x of arr) {
            map.set(x, (map.get(x) || 0) + 1);
     }

9) hashset
     let set = new Set()
     set.has(1)
     set.add(1)
     set.size;
     no duplicate array [...new Set(arr)];
      to convert to array [...set];

10) Stack 
     let stack = [];
     stack.push(x);
     stack.pop();
     stack[stack.length - 1]; 
